data.title: Emma Delucchi - Women's Rowing
data.meta_description: Emma Delucchi - 2017-18: Placed 19th overall in the varsity four boat at the NCAA Championships…notched a first-place victory in the varsity four at the WCC Championships…finished
data.text:
2017-18: Placed 19th overall in the varsity four boat at the NCAA Championships…notched a first-place victory in the varsity four at the WCC Championships…finished second in the varsity four boat in the Fawley Cup vs. Washington State…had another second place finish in the second varsity four at the Lake Natoma Invitational…defeated Oregon State in the second varsity four…finished ninth in the second varsity four at the San Diego Crew Classic…took second in the varsity four at the Hornet Invite…placed fourth at the Head of the Lake in the second varsity eight…took fourth at the Head of the Spokane in the Head of the Spokane…Honorable Mention WCC All-Academic Team.

2016-17: Defeated Washington State in the Fawley Cup with the fourth varsity eight … defeated WSU with the third varsity eight in the fall’s Head of the Spokane … WCC All-Academic Honorable Mention.

2015-16: Took first in the varsity four boat at the Portland Fall Classic… took third at the Head of the Lake in the third varsity eight boat…defeated Oregon State in the second varsity four boat…took second in the open eight boat at the San Diego Crew Classic.

HIGH SCHOOL: Graduated from Holy Names Academy in Seattle…rowed crew and finished ninth at the 2013 USA Youth Nationals in the varsity four boat…went to the Northwest High Performance Camp…was most Inspirational Player in 2011 and on the US Rowing Honor Roll in 2015…earned National Hispanic Scholar recognition and was a member of the National Honor Society and an AP Scholar with a 4.2 GPA.
